20pounds%20of%20tritium%20each.%20The%20world's%20largest%20fusion%20project%2C%20ITER%20might%20not%20get%20up%20and%20running%20until%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Fwhat-is-the-future-of-fusion-energy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2040s%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20it's%20being%20used%20for%20research%20instead%20of%20commercial%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20ITER's%20main%20goals%20is%20to%20produce%20a%20burning%20plasma.%20An%20international%20collaboration%20between%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20the%20US%2C%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20other%20countries%2C%20it's%20also%20way%20over%20budget.%20Originally%20expected%20to%20be%20up%20and%20running%20by%202016%20for%20around%20%246.3%20billion%2C%20it's%20now%20several%20years%20behind%20and%20over%20three%20times%20the%20original%20cost%20estimate%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Fworlds-largest-fusion-project-is-in-big-trouble-new-documents-reveal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScientific%20American%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHurdle%203%3A%20Containing%20something%20hotter%20than%20the%20sun%20is%20difficult%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECreating%20a%20magnetic%20containment%20device%20to%20hold%20plasma%20is%20its%20own%20challenge.%20Plasma%20needs%20to%20reach%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iter.org%2Fmag%2F2%2F18%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etemperatures%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20150%20million%20degrees%20Celsius%20and%20above.%20That's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-if-humans-tried-landing-sun-2020-2%5C%22%3Ehotter%20than%20the%20sun%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20most%20heat-resistant%20metal%20container%20can't%20hold%20the%20plasma.%20Any%20material%20would%20get%20damaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224444%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20a%20gold-plated%20hohlraum%20from%20the%20National%20Ignition%20Facility%20glows%20green%20against%20a%20black%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653183e296f7540cd060d724%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20National%20Ignition%20Facility's%20192%20laser%20beams%20are%20aimed%20at%20a%20hohlraum%2C%20which%20holds%20the%20deuterium%20and%20tritium%20capsule.%3Cp%3EJason%20Laurea%2FLawrence%20Livermore%20National%20Laboratory%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iaea.org%2Fnewscenter%2Fnews%2Ftokamaks-stellarators-laser-based-and-alternative-concepts-report-offers-global-perspective-on-nuclear-fusion-devices%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20common%3C%2Fa%3E%20plasma-confinement%20solutions%20is%20a%20tokamak.%20The%20device%20functions%20as%20a%20kind%20of%20%26quot%3Bmagnetic%20bottle.%26quot%3B%20The%20plasma%20particles%20follow%20the%20invisible%20lines%20of%20the%20magnetic%20field%20and%20don't%20stray%20beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHurdle%204%3A%20It's%20a%20finicky%20reaction%20%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20metal%20plasma-containment%20device%20would%20also%20cool%20the%20contents%20and%20stop%20the%20fusion%20process.%20That's%20one%20reason%20fusion%20reactors%20can't%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchernobyl-nuclear-disaster-strange-events-afterwards-2019-7%5C%22%3EChernobyl-like%20meltdowns%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20such%20a%20finicky%20reaction%20that%20disturbances%20cause%20it%20to%20cool%20down%20and%20stop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20plasma%20can%20behave%20weirdly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20when%20you're%20squeezing%20Jell-O%20in%20your%20hand%2C%26quot%3B%20Christlieb%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20finds%20these%20little%20holes%20to%20squeeze%20out%20of%20because%20your%20hand%20isn't%20perfectly%20sealed.%26quot%3B%20The%20tokamak%20has%20to%20be%20able%20to%20adapt%20to%20the%20changes%20in%20the%20plasma.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20plasma%20changes%20its%20behavior%2C%20it%20can%20interact%20with%20and%20damage%20the%20wall%20of%20the%20device.%20The%20Princeton%20lab%20is%20experimenting%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pppl.gov%2Fresearch%2Fprojects%2Flithium-tokamak-experiment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliquid%20metal%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20some%20fusion%20reactor%20components.%20Jonathan%20Menard%2C%20chief%20research%20officer%20at%20the%20Princeton%20Plasma%20Physics%20Laboratory%2C%20compares%20it%20to%20the%20T-1000%20in%20%26quot%3BTerminator%202%2C%26quot%3B%20making%20it%20almost%20self-repairing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHurdle%205%3A%20Tritium%20is%20still%20radioactive%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20tritium%20has%20a%20much%20shorter%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nrc.gov%2Freading-rm%2Fdoc-collections%2Ffact-sheets%2Fradwaste.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehalf-life%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20Plutonium-239%20(12.3%20years%20compared%20to%2024%2C000%20years)%2C%20the%20former%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcen.acs.org%2Farticles%2F84%2Fi26%2FRadioactive-Leaks-Found-Reactors.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeen%20known%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20leak%20into%20groundwater%20from%20nuclear%20power%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelion-energy-fusion-company-backed-by-sam-altman-and-microsoft-2023-5%5C%22%3Efusion%20power%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20a%20brand%20new%20type%20of%20facility%2C%20there%20are%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fnuclear-fusion-a-clean-energy-revolution-or-a-radioactive-nightmare-1032400280%5C%22%3Ea%20lot%20of%20unknowns%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20other%20safety%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20report%20looked%20at%20everything%20from%20earthquakes%20to%20fires%20to%20terror%20attacks.%20Some%20scenarios%2C%20like%20electromagnetic%20discharge%20%E2%80%94%20where%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0920379619308737%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emagnet%20systems%20fail%20and%20cause%20the%20energy%20to%20arc%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20accidents%20involving%20breeder%20blankets%20need%20further%20study%2C%20the%20authors%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EExperts%20think%20it'll%20take%20decades%20for%20commercial%20fusion%20power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20large%20number%20of%20challenges%2C%20both%20Menard%20and%20Christlieb%20were%20optimistic%20about%20the%20future%20of%20fusion%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20still%20some%20way%20off.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20single%20digits%2C%26quot%3B%20Menard%20said.%20It's%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20perennial%20joke%20about%20fusion%20is%20it's%20always%2010%20years%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20Christlieb%20said.%20But%20he%20does%20think%20it's%20closer%20than%20ever%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20government%20has%20invested%20in%20fusion%20energy%20since%20the%201950s.%20The%20US%20Department%20of%20Energy's%20Fusion%20Energy%20Sciences%20program%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrsreports.congress.gov%2Fproduct%2Fpdf%2FIF%2FIF12411%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24763%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20budget%20for%202023%2C%20which%20could%20grow%20to%20over%20%241%20billion%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fusionindustryassociation.org%2Ffusion-industry-reports%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFusion%20Industry%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%20puts%20overall%20fu