lligence%20chiefs%20on%20the%20X%20platform%2C%20saying%20they%20never%20warned%20him%20Hamas%20was%20planning%20its%20wide-scale%20attack%20on%20Oct.%207%2C%20but%20later%20retracted%20his%20comments%20and%20issued%20an%20apology.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20remarks%2C%20posted%20on%20X%20at%201%20a.m.%20on%20Sunday%20(around%202300%20GMT%20on%20Saturday)%2C%20caused%20a%20political%20uproar%20and%20a%20rift%20within%20the%20war%20cabinet%20of%20Netanyahu%2C%20who%20has%20drawn%20public%20ire%20for%20not%20taking%20responsibility%20over%20intelligence%20and%20operational%20failures%20relating%20to%20Hamas'%20rampage%20through%20southern%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20top%20officials%20-%20from%20the%20heads%20of%20the%20military%20and%20the%20Shin%20Bet%20domestic%20spy%20service%20to%20his%20finance%20minister%20-%20have%20all%20acknowledged%20their%20failures%2C%20Netanyahu%20has%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20only%20said%20that%20there%20would%20be%20time%20to%20ask%20tough%20questions%2C%20including%20of%20himself%2C%20after%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael's%20military%20spokesperson%2C%20asked%20about%20Netanyahu's%20comments%20during%20a%20daily%20briefing%20with%20reporters%2C%20declined%20to%20respond%2C%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20now%20at%20war%2C%20focused%20on%20the%20war.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20officials%20have%20said%20events%20leading%20up%20to%20and%20including%20the%20handling%20of%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20itself%20would%20be%20investigated%2C%20but%20that%20the%20current%20focus%20was%20on%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENetanyahu's%20now-deleted%20post%20had%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BAt%20no%20time%20and%20no%20stage%20was%20a%20warning%20given%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Netanyahu%20regarding%20war%20intentions%20of%20Hamas.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20all%20security%20officials%2C%20including%20the%20head%20of%20army%20intelligence%20and%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Shin%20Bet%2C%20estimated%20that%20Hamas%20was%20deterred%20and%20interested%20in%20an%20arrangement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20second%20post%20on%20X%20about%2010%20hours%20later%2C%20Netanyahu%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20his%20remarks%20%26quot%3Bshould%20not%20have%20been%20made%20and%20I%20apologize%20for%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20give%20full%20backing%20to%20all%20the%20heads%20of%20the%20security%20branches%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENetanyahu's%20initial%20comments%20were%20promptly%20rebuked%20by%20current%20and%20past%20allies%2C%20including%20Benny%20Gantz%2C%20a%20former%20defense%20minister%20who%20is%20now%20in%20Netanyahu's%20war%20cabinet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGantz%20said%20on%20X%20that%20Netanyahu%20should%20retract%20what%20he%20said%20and%20let%20the%20matter%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20are%20at%20war%2C%20leadership%20must%20show%20responsibility%2C%20decide%20to%20do%20the%20right%20things%20and%20bolster%20the%20forces%20in%20a%20way%20that%20they%20can%20carry%20out%20what%20we%20demand%20of%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Gantz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20well-planned%20surprise%20Hamas%20attack%20was%20the%20deadliest%20for%20Israel%20in%20its%2075-year%20history.%20Israel%20has%20since%20bombarded%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20with%20devastating%20air%20strikes%20and%20begun%20ground%20operations%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20toppling%20the%20Iran-backed%20Islamist%20group%20and%20securing%20the%20release%20of%20scores%20of%20people%20abducted%20from%20Israel%20to%20Gaza%20on%20Oct.%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOpposition%20leader%20Yair%20Lapid%2C%20who%20was%20formerly%20prime%20minister%2C%20said%20Netanyahu%20%26quot%3Bcrossed%20a%20red%20line%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20overnight%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20attempts%20to%20evade%20responsibility%20and%20place%20the%20blame%20on%20the%20security%20establishment%20weakens%20the%20IDF%20(Israel%20Defense%20Forces)%20while%20it's%20fighting%20Israel's%20enemies%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYossi%20Cohen%2C%20who%20headed%20the%20Mossad%20spy%20agency%20under%20previous%20Netanyahu%20governments%2C%20told%20Israel%20Radio%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20take%20responsibility%20from%20the%20beginning%20of%20your%20job%2C%20not%20from%20the%20middle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698579240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fhg1mlvo_netanyahu-israel--pm_625x300_24_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-pm-benjamin-netanyahu-takes-jab-at-intel-chiefs-over-hamas-attack-later-apologises-4525355%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20on%20Sunday%20took%20a%20jab%20at%20his%20intelligence%20chiefs%20on%20the%20X%20platform%2C%20saying%20they%20never%20warned%20him%20Hamas%20was%20planning%20its%20wide-scale%20attack%20on%20Oct.%207%2C%20but%20later%20retracted%20his%20comments%20and%20issued%20an%20apology.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-pm-benjamin-netanyahu-takes-jab-at-intel-chiefs-over-hamas-attack-later-apologises-4525355%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-pm-benjamin-netanyahu-takes-jab-at-intel-chiefs-over-hamas-attack-later-apologises-4525355%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-pm-benjamin-netanyahu-takes-jab-at-intel-chiefs-over-hamas-attack-later-apologises-4525355%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22South%20Africa%20Rugby%20World%20Cup%3A%20The%20Springboks%20give%20hope%20to%20a%20troubled%20nation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A16985789520