20bombardment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Egyptian%20leader%20highlighted%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccritical%20need%20for%20unified%20international%20action%20to%20find%20a%20prompt%20solution%20at%20the%20diplomatic%20level%2C%20that%20stipulates%20reinforcing%20an%20immediate%20humanitarian%20truce%20that%20protects%20the%20lives%20of%20civilians%20and%20allows%20the%20instantaneous%2C%20sustainable%20and%20unfettered%20delivery%20of%20humanitarian%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHis%20words%20echoed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.un.org%2Fen%2F2023%2Fga12548.doc.htm%5C%22%3Eprovisions%20of%20the%20UNGA%20resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20adopted%20with%20120%20votes%20in%20favour%2C%2014%20against%20and%2045%20abstentions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20developing%20world%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20India%20has%20been%20a%20outlier%20in%20not%20voting%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698559640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F25200857%2Fimage-1086.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-calls-up-egyptian-president-discusses-israeli-military-actions-in-gaza%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20talk%20takes%20place%20in%20the%20backdrop%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20unannounced%20ground%20invasion%20of%20Gaza%20strip%2C%20after%2020%20days%20of%20retaliatory%20airstrikes%20which%20have%20reportedly%20left%20over%207%2C000%20dead.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-calls-up-egyptian-president-discusses-israeli-military-actions-in-gaza%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Three%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%3A%20Using%20Criminal%20Law%20to%20Establish%20Permanent%20Extra-Constitutional%20Emergency%20Powers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F29015445%2FIMG_2557.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%C2%A0%3Cem%3EStrong%20Societies%20and%20Weak%20States%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1988%2C%20Princeton%20University%20Press)%20Joel%20S.%20Migdal%20quotes%20Eugene%20Weber%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EPeasants%20into%20Frenchmen%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1976%2C%20Stanford%20University%20Press)%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20one%20section%20of%20France%2C%20the%20evening%20prayers%20of%20peasants%20long%20included%20the%20line%2C%20%E2%80%98Deliver%20us%20from%20all%20evil%20and%20from%20justice.%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20If%20the%20three%20bills%20presented%20to%20Parliament%20by%20the%20Union%20Government%20in%20August%20this%20year%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%2C%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%20and%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%2C1973%20are%20enacted%20into%20law%2C%20we%20Indians%20would%20do%20well%20to%20also%20incorporate%20in%20our%20daily%20prayers%20a%20plea%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdeliver%20us%20from%20criminal%20justice%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2011%2C%202023%20the%20Union%20Government%20introduced%20three%20new%20Bills%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%20(the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%20referred%20to%20here%20for%20ease%20of%20reference%20as%20%E2%80%9CBNS-IPC%E2%80%9D)%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%20(the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Adhiniyam%20Bill%2C%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%9CBSA-IEA%E2%80%9D)%20and%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%2C%201973%20(the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%9CBNSS-CrPC%E2%80%9D).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EQuantitatively%2C%20the%20bills%20only%20change%20some%2020%25-25%25%20of%20the%20law%20in%20the%20three%20current%20statutes%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EQualitatively%2C%20the%20changes%20consist%20mostly%20of%20an%20extensive%20(and%20entirely%20needless)%20re-ordering%20and%20re-numbering%20of%20the%20provisions%20to%20pretend%20that%20the%20laws%20have%20been%20slimmed%20down%3B%20several%20anodyne%20amendments%20to%20facilitate%20electronic%20proceedings%3B%20several%20largely%20non-consequential%20changes%20of%20nomenclature%3B%20and%20yet%20another%20unrealistic%20legislative%20attempt%20to%20set%20timelines%20on%20court%20proceedings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20changes%20also%20include%20long%20demanded%20de-criminalisation%20of%20the%20attempt%20to%20commit%20suicide%20(except%20when%20directed%20against%20public%20officials%2C%20see%20below)%2C%20homosexuality%20(although%20the%20wholesale%20deletion%20of%20S.377%2C%20IPC%20will%20create%20a%20number%20of%20serious%20issues)%20and%20adultery%20(although%20there%20is%20some%20indication%20that%20a%20gender-neutral%20prohibition%20on%20adultery%20may%20be%20demanded%20by%20the%20BJP-run%20select%20committee).%20There%20are%20welcome%20changes%20on%20gender%20equalisation%20and%20clearer%20criminalisation%20of%20gang%20rape%20of%20women%20below%20the%20age%20of%2018%2C%20use%20of%20a%20child%20to%20commit%20offences%2C%20lynching%20and%20snatching.%20The%20amendments%20also%20mandate%20videography%20during%20some%20of%20stages%20of%20investigation.%20There%20are%20controversial%20changes%20criminalising%20sexual%20intercourse%20by%20employing%20deceitful%20means%20and%20replacing%20the%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%98incapability%20to%20form%20intent%E2%80%99%20with%20%E2%80%98mental%20illness.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETwelve%20chilling%20changes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20crucial%20and%20requires%20very%20close%20public%20attention%2C%20however%2C%20are%20a%20dozen%20chilling%20changes%20to%20the%20law%20that%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20liquidate%20liberty%2C%20decimate%20democracy%20and%20fundamentally%20change%20the%20face%20of%20our%20polity%20from%20democratic%20to%20authoritarian%20should%20the%20government%20decide%20to%20deploy%20any%20or%20all%20of%20these%20changes%20to%20their%20fullest%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESix%20of%20the%2012%20sets%20of%20changes%20create%20powerful%20weapons%20to%20silence%20dissent%2C%20decimate%20opposition%20and%20shut%20down%20public%20discourse.%20Of%20these%2C%20three%20sets%20of%20changes%20add%20new%20weapons%20for%20targeted%2C%20biased%2C%20political%20persecution%20(TBPP)%20through%20prosecution%20and%20incarceration%20of%20individuals%20and%20organisations%20deemed%20by%20ruling%20ideologue%20to%20be%20its%20enemies%3B%20two%20attack%20direct%20democratic%20action%3B%20and%20one%20is%20a%20partisan%20exercise%20of%20legislative%20power%20to%20facilitate%20the%20Sangh%20Parivar%E2%80%99s%20work%20against%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFive%20other%20sets%20of%20changes%20exponentially%20enhance%20police%20raj.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%2012th%20set%20of%20changes%20intensifies%20the%20pain%20and%20suffering%20of%20those%20who%20are%20targeted%20for%20democratic%20thought%20and%20action%20through%20enhanced%20incarceration%2C%20including%20in%20police%20custody.%20It%20seems%20also%20like%20a%20frisson%20of%20schadenfreude%20for%20the%20rulers%20(pleasure%20derived%20from%20another%20person%E2%80%99s%20suffering).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETaken%20together%2C%20these%2012%20changes%2C%20in%20conjunction%20with%20cognate%20changes%20not%20detailed%20here%2C%20will%20result%20in%20a%20quantum%20leap%20in%20the%20power%20of%20the%20government%20to%20use%20criminal%20law%2C%20if%20and%20when%20it%20so%20wishes%2C%20as%20an%20effective%20weapon%20to%20silence%20dissent%20and%20opposition%20and%20shut%20down%20public%20discourse%2C%20choking%20all%20channels%20that%20communicate%20conflicting%20news%20or%20views%20to%20the%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Bills%2C%20if%20enacted%2C%20will%20establish%20permanent%20extra-constitutional%20emergency%20powers%20in%20India%20through%20statutory%20means.%20Future%20governments%20are%20unlikely%20to%20surrender%20this%20power%20or%20revoke%20this%20extra-constitutional%20emergency.%20What%20makes%20this%20possible%20is%20that%20these%20new%20criminal%20laws%20do%20not%20reflect%20constitutional%20morality.%20They%20have%20no%20in-built%20constitutional%20constraints.%20They%20are%20anti-Constitutional%20in%20letter%20and%20spirit.%20The%20overall%20aim%20of%20the%20two%20Sanhitas%20and%20the%20Adhiniyam%20may%20perhaps%20best%20be%20summed%20up%20by%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fanti-india-separatist-corrupt-ecosystem-in-jk-no-space-to-breathe-manoj-sinha-8983045%2F%5C%22%3E%20sentiment%20expressed%20recently%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Right%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20of%20Jammu%2C%20Kashmir%20and%20Ladakh%3A%20%E2%80%9CDon%E2%80%99t%20give%20them%20space%20to%20breathe!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20without%20doubt%20at%20a%20dawn%20that%20comes%20before%20a%20night%20of%20deep%20darkness.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty-300x150.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty-1024x512.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty-800x400.png%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-660898%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20three%20changes%20discussed%20create%20new%20weapons%20for%20targeted%2C%20biased%2C%20political%20persecution%20(TBPP)%20through%20prosecution%20and%20incarceration%20against%20those%20who%20are%20deemed%20enemies%20of%20the%20ruling%20ideologues%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI.%20Arbitrary%20power%20to%20label%20non-violent%20democratic%20action%20as%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98t%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Eerrorism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20of%20the%20chilling%20statutory%20changes%20gives%20the%20government%20arbitrary%20power%20to%20label%20virtually%20any%20non-violent%20action%20for%20democracy%20or%20social%2C%20political%20or%20economic%20justice%2C%20or%20any%20non-violent%20dissent%2C%20protest%20or%20opposition%2C%20or%20public%20discourse%20that%20conflicts%20with%20the%20government%20narrative%2C%20as%20%E2%80%9Cterrorism%E2%80%9D%20and%20unleash%20the%20full%20force%20of%20anti-terrorism%20laws%20to%20smash%20and%20silence%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20draconian%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20in%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%2C%201967%20(UAPA)%20includes%20enumerated%20violent%20acts%20that%20aim%20to%20%E2%80%9Cthreaten%20or%20%5Bare%5D%20likely%20to%20threaten%20the%20unity%2C%20integrity%2C%20security%2C%20economic%20security%2C%20or%20sovereignty%20of%20India%20or%20%5Bare%20done%5D%20with%20intent%20to%20strike%20terror%20or%20likely%20to%20strike%20terror%20in%20the%20people%20or%20any%20section%20of%20the%20people%20in%20India%20or%20in%20any%20foreign%20country%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EClause%20111(1)(iv)%20of%20BNS-IPC%20widens%20the%20UAPA%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20in%20two%20ways.%20(1)%20Under%20UAPA%20an%20act%20must%20be%20a%20violent%20act%20to%20be%20considered%20a%20terrorist%20act.%20BNS-IPC%20adds%20peaceful%2C%20non-violent%20acts%20to%20the%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20if%20they%20meet%20other%20relevant%20criteria.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20under%20BNS-IPC%20even%20a%20non-violent%20act%2C%20or%20a%20mere%20expression%20through%20speech%20or%20writing%20will%20fall%20within%20the%20definition%20of%20terrorism.%20(2)%20Under%20UAPA%20an%20act%20should%20%E2%80%9Cstrike%20terror%20in%20the%20people%20or%20any%20section%20thereof%E2%80%9D%20%3Cspan%3Ei%3C%2Fspan%3En%20order%20to%20be%20a%20terrorist%20act.%20BNS%20widens%20the%20net%20of%20terrorism%20and%20makes%20all%20acts%20that%20%E2%80%9Cintimidate%20the%20general%20public%20or%20a%20segment%20thereof%E2%80%9D%20to%20be%20considered%20terrorist%20acts.%20BNS-IPC%20also%20adds%20a%20very%20broad%20criterion%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdisturbance%20of%20public%20order%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20definition%20of%20terrorist%20act.%20BNS-IPC%20also%20adds%20a%20new%20ground%20to%20the%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20to%20further%20widen%20its%20net%3A%20an%20act%20is%20terrorist%20if%20it%20%E2%80%9Cdestabilises%20or%20destroys%20the%20political%2C%20economic%2C%20or%20social%20structures%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%20This%20last%20ground%20echoes%20the%20European%20Council%20Framework%20Decision%20of%2013%20June%202002%20under%20which%20terrorism%20is%20defined%20as%20offences%20under%20national%20law%20committed%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20%E2%80%9Cseriously%20destabilising%20or%20destroying%20the%20fundamental%20political%2C%20constitutional%2C%20economic%20or%20social%20structures%20of%20a%20country%20or%20an%20international%20organisation%E2%80%9D.%20The%20BNS-IPC%20definition%20drops%20the%20European%20requirement%20that%20only%20%E2%80%9Coffences%E2%80%9D%20established%20under%20a%20statute%20can%20be%20included%20in%20the%20definition%20of%20terrorism.%20BNS-IPC%20also%20drops%20the%20European%20Council%20requirement%20that%20in%20order%20for%20an%20act%20to%20be%20considered%20a%20terrorist%20act%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdestablisation%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cdestruction%E2%80%9D%20must%20be%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cserious%E2%80%9D%20nature%20and%20the%20political%2C%20constitutional%2C%20economic%20or%20social%20structures%20attacked%20must%20be%20%E2%80%9Cfundamental%E2%80%9D%20structures.%20This%20way%2C%20BNS-IPC%20greatly%20broadens%20the%20ambit%20of%20its%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20well%20beyond%20accepted%20legal%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22How%20Consultative%20Was%20the%20Framing%20of%20the%20Three%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%2C%20Really%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-consultative-was-the-framing-of-the-three-criminal-law-bills-really%5C%22%3EHow%20Consultative%20Was%20the%20Framing%20of%20the%20Three%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%2C%20Really%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitution%20of%20India%20(Article%2038)%20unambiguously%20calls%20on%20the%20State%20to%20secure%20a%20social%20order%20for%20the%20promotion%20of%20welfare%20of%20the%20people%20in%20which%20justice%20%E2%80%94%20social%2C%20economic%20and%20political%20%E2%80%94%20shall%20inform%20all%20institutions%20of%20national%20life.%20The%20Constitution%20commands%20the%20State%20%E2%80%9Cin%20particular%2C%20%5Bto%5D%20strive%20to%20minimise%20the%20inequalities%20in%20income%2C%20and%20endeavour%20to%20eliminate%20inequalities%20in%20status%2C%20facilities%20and%20opportunities%2C%20not%20only%20amongst%20individuals%20but%20also%20amongst%20groups%20of%20people%20residing%20in%20different%20areas%20or%20engaged%20in%20different%20vocations.%E2%80%9D%20These%20changes%20cannot%20be%20done%20without%20non-violently%20%E2%80%98destroying%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98destabilising%E2%80%99%2C%20to%20a%20greater%20or%20lesser%20extent%2C%20the%20feudal%2C%20theocratic%20social%2C%20political%20and%20economic%20order%20that%20has%20dominated%20the%20country%20for%20centuries.%20These%20changes%20will%20inevitably%20%E2%80%99divide%E2%80%99%20people%20into%20those%20who%20want%20the%20revolutionary%20changes%20and%20the%20elites%20who%20oppose%20them%20and%20are%20%E2%80%98intimidated%E2%80%99%20by%20them.%20The%20BNS-IPC%20provision%20puts%20all%20peaceful%20movements%20for%20revolutionary%20social%2C%20political%20and%20economic%20changes%20at%20risk%20of%20being%20prosecuted%20as%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%E2%80%9D%20movements%20(these%20may%20include%20for%20example%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20call%20for%20%E2%80%9Cannihilating%20caste%E2%80%9D%20and%20movements%20against%20patriarchy%20or%20capitalism).%20In%20this%20context%2C%20it%20is%20significant%20that%20acts%20against%20the%20%E2%80%9Csocial%20structures%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%9D%20which%20are%20not%20in%20the%20UAPA%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20have%20been%20included%20in%20the%20BNS-IPC%20terrorism%20definition.%20This%20appears%20to%20signal%20an%20intention%20to%20use%20anti-terror%20tools%20to%20fight%20social%20reform%20that%20threatens%20the%20current%20caste-based%20social%20order.%C2%A0%20The%20significance%20of%20the%20convenient%20omission%20of%20attacks%20on%20the%20constitutional%20structure%20from%20the%20BNS-IPC%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20is%20discussed%20later%20in%20this%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20and%20open-ended%20provisions%20on%20terrorism%20introduced%20in%20BNS-IPC%20will%20co-exist%20with%20already%20existing%20sweeping%20criminalisation%20of%20terrorism%20under%20The%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%2C%201967%20which%20includes%20three%20chapters%20on%20terrorism.%C2%A0%20These%20two%20sets%20of%20laws%20against%20terrorism%20are%20not%20identical.%20Those%20prosecuted%20for%20terrorism%20under%20BNS-IPC%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20avail%20of%20(the%20slim)%20protection%20measures%20available%20to%20them%20under%20the%20UAPA%20provisions%20and%20the%20special%20courts%20established%20under%20them.%20Those%20targeted%20could%20be%20prosecuted%20and%20convicted%20under%20both%20sets%20of%20laws%20and%20face%20interminable%20imprisonment.%20We%20may%20presume%20that%20this%20heavy%20deterrent%20against%20questioning%20the%20established%20social%20structure%20on%20pain%20of%20punishment%20for%20terrorism%20is%20intended%20to%20preserve%20the%20inequitable%20social%20structure%20of%20the%20country%20and%20to%20stave%20off%20much%20needed%2C%20revolutionary%2C%20peaceful%20social%20change%20envisaged%20in%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EII.%20Sedition%20is%20reborn%20as%20sedition%20plus%20%E2%80%94%20in%20a%20more%20vicious%20avatar%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20attack%20against%20liberty%2C%20democracy%2C%20dissent%20and%20opposition%20is%20the%20new%20channel%20that%20BNS-IPC%20opens%20up%20for%20targeted%2C%20biased%2C%20political%20persecution%20(TBPP)%20through%20prosecution%20and%20incarceration%C2%A0%20of%20opponents%20and%20dissidents%20through%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20new%2C%20ill-defined%2C%20over-broad%20mega-crime%20(%E2%80%9CActs%20endangering%20sovereignty%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%2C%20Clause%20150%20of%20BNS-IPC).%20Clause%20150%20criminalises%20five%20activities%3A%20(1)%20%E2%80%9Csubversive%20activities%E2%80%9D%3B%20%E2%80%9C(2)%20secession%E2%80%9D%3B%20(3)%20%E2%80%9Cseparatist%20activities%E2%80%9D%3B%20(4)%20%E2%80%9Cendangering%20sovereignty%2C%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Carmed%20rebellion%E2%80%9D.%20None%20of%20them%20is%20statutorily%20defined%2C%20leaving%20unbounded%20discretion%20to%20the%20police%20and%20political%20executive.%20Clause%20150%20criminalises%20three%20types%20of%20ridiculously%20vague%20and%20undefinable%20methods%20by%20which%20these%20five%20activities%20may%20be%20undertaken%3A%20(1)%20%E2%80%9Cexciting%E2%80%9D%20people%20in%20support%20of%20these%20prohibited%20activities%2C%20(2)%20%E2%80%9Ccreation%20of%20excitement%20amongst%20people%E2%80%9D%20in%20a%20positive%20way%20towards%20these%20activities%3B%20and%20(3)%20encouragement%20of%20feelings%20amongst%20people%E2%80%9D%20in%20favour%20of%20these%20activities.%20Clause%20150%20creates%20four%20prohibited%20instruments%20through%20which%20such%20crimes%20may%20be%20committed.%20Two%20are%20new%3A(1)%20electronic%20communication%3B%20and%20(2)%20financial%20means.%20Three%20are%20copied%20from%20IPC%20Section%20124A%20(sedition)%3A%20(1)%20%E2%80%9Cwords%2C%20either%20spoken%20or%20written%E2%80%9D%2C%20(2)%20%E2%80%9Csigns%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9C(3)%20visible%20representation%E2%80%9D.%20These%20prohibited%20activities%2C%20methods%20and%20instruments%20are%20defined%20using%20such%20broad%20and%20vague%20language%20that%20any%20government%20will%20be%20able%20to%20target%20virtually%20anyone%20who%20the%20government%20wants%20neutralized%20or%20silenced%2C%20and%20to%20crush%20honest%2C%20democratic%20and%20non-violent%20expressions%20of%20dissent%20and%20opposition%20in%20the%20same%20way%20as%20has%20been%20done%20from%20colonial%20to%20contemporary%20times%20under%20Section%20124A%20(sedition).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESection%20124A%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%20(sedition)%20is%20not%20included%20in%20BNS-IPC.%20The%20Union%20claims%20this%20deletion%20of%20Section%20124A%20is%20a%20liberal%20revision%20of%20criminal%20law.%20The%20IPC%20crime%20of%20sedition%20is%20basically%20%E2%80%98the%20creation%20of%2C%20or%20any%20attempt%20to%20create%E2%80%99%2C%20one%20or%20more%20of%20five%20sets%20of%20negative%20attitudes%20towards%20the%20government%3A%20(i)%20%E2%80%9Chatred%E2%80%9D%20(ii)%20%E2%80%9Ccontempt%E2%80%9D%20(iii)%20%E2%80%9Cdisaffection%E2%80%9D%3B%20(iv)%20%E2%80%9Cdisloyalty%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20(v)%20%E2%80%9Cenmity%E2%80%9D.%20While%20deleting%20Section%20124A%2C%20Clause%20150%20of%20BNS-IPC%20criminalises%20a%20much%20broader%20range%20of%20activities%20arising%20from%20such%20attitudes.%20Clause%20150%20is%20a%20reincarnation%20of%20Section%20124A%20in%20an%20even%20more%20vicious%20avatar%20%E2%80%94%20sedition%20is%20dead%2C%20long%20live%20sedition%20plus!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15112516%2Fimg_2622-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15112516%2Fimg_2622-2.jpg%201080w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15112516%2Fimg_2622-2-300x120.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15112516%2Fimg_2622-2-1024x410.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668157%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22432%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIII.%20Enabling%20targeting%20of%20dissidents%20and%20political%20opponents%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20attack%20on%20democracy%20is%20also%2C%20like%20the%20first%20two%2C%20a%20new%20legal%20weapon%20for%20targeted%2C%20biased%2C%20political%20persecution%20through%20prosecution%20(TBPP)%20against%20those%20who%20do%20not%20fall%20in%20line%20with%20the%20government%20and%20its%20social%2C%20economic%20and%20political%20masters%20(in%20addition%20to%20the%20two%20just%20discussed).%20This%20weapon%20consists%20of%20implicating%20its%20victims%20in%20organised%20crime%20(Clause%20109)%20and%20petty%20organised%20crime%20(Clause%20110).%20Existing%20draconian%20laws%20on%20organised%20crime%20such%20as%20Maharashtra%20Control%20of%20Organised%20Crime%20Act%2C%201999%20(MCOCA)%20and%20Karnataka%20Control%20of%20Organised%20Crimes%20Act%2C%202000%20(KCOCA)%20provide%20definitions%20of%20organised%20crime.%20Under%20MCOCA%20and%20KCOCA%20%E2%80%9Corganised%20crime%E2%80%9D%20is%20defined%20as%20%E2%80%9Cany%20continuing%20unlawful%20activity%20by%20an%20individual%2C%20singly%20or%20jointly%2C%20either%20as%20a%20member%20of%20an%20organised%20crime%20syndicate%20or%20on%20behalf%20of%20such%20syndicate%2C%20by%20use%20of%20violence%20or%20threat%20of%20violence%20or%20intimidation%20or%20coercion%2C%20or%20other%20unlawful%20means%2C%20with%20the%20objective%20of%20gaining%20pecuniary%20benefits%2C%20or%20gaining%20undue%20economic%20or%20other%20advantage%20for%20himself%20or%20any%20other%20person%20or%20promoting%20insurgency%E2%80%9D.%20The%20United%20Nations%20Convention%20against%20Transnational%20Organized%20Crime%2C%202000%20also%20provides%20an%20established%20definition%20of%20organized%20crime%3A%20%E2%80%9CAgreeing%20with%20one%20or%20more%20other%20persons%20to%20commit%20a%20serious%20crime%20for%20a%20purpose%20relating%20directly%20or%20indirectly%20to%20the%20obtaining%20of%20a%20financial%20or%20other%20material%20benefit%20and%2C%20where%20required%20by%20domestic%20law%2C%20involving%20an%20act%20undertaken%20by%20one%20of%20the%20participants%20in%20furtherance%20of%20the%20agreement%20or%20involving%20an%20organized%20criminal%20group.%E2%80%9D%20In%20contrast%2C%20BNS-IPC%20introduces%20a%20new%20definition%20of%20organised%20crime%20that%20is%20riddled%20with%20lack%20of%20clarity%3A%20%E2%80%9CAny%20continuing%20unlawful%20activity%20including%20kidnapping%2C%20robbery%2C%20vehicle%20theft%2C%20extortion%2C%20land%20grabbing%2C%20contract%20killing%2C%20economic%20offences%2C%20cyber-crimes%20having%20severe%20consequences%2C%20trafficking%20in%20people%2C%20drugs%2C%20illicit%20goods%20or%20services%20and%20weapons%2C%20human%20trafficking%20racket%20for%20prostitution%20or%20ransom%20by%20the%20effort%20of%20groups%20of%20individuals%20acting%20in%20concert%2C%20singly%20or%20jointly%2C%20either%20as%20a%20member%20of%20an%20organised%20crime%20syndicate%20or%20on%20behalf%20of%C2%A0%20such%20syndicate%2C%20by%20use%20of%20violence%2C%20threat%20of%20violence%2C%20intimidation%2C%20coercion%2C%20corruption%20or%20related%20activities%20or%20other%20unlawful%20means%20to%20obtain%20direct%20or%20indirect%2C%20material%20benefit%20including%20a%20financial%20benefit%2C%20shall%20constitute%20organised%20crime.%E2%80%9D%20If%20there%20was%20need%20to%20create%20a%20new%20national%20offence%20on%20organised%20crime%2C%20why%20is%20a%20new%20and%20thoroughly%20confusing%20definition%20of%20organised%20crime%20used%20rather%20than%20the%20relatively%20clearer%20definitions%20that%20are%20available%20in%20state%20legislation%20and%20internationally%20%E2%80%94%20if%20not%20just%20to%20be%20able%20to%20misuse%20and%20abuse%20the%20provision%20to%20pursue%20and%20neutralise%20political%20and%20ideological%20opponents%3F%20If%20the%20intention%20is%20to%20seriously%20address%20the%20very%20grave%20problem%20of%20organised%20crime%20a%20professional%20and%20bona%20fide%20approach%20to%20the%20drafting%20of%20the%20offence%20is%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIV.%20Attacking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3Efasting%20as%20political%20protest%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20assault%20on%20our%20democratic%20rights%20is%20the%20criminalisation%20of%20the%20use%20of%20fasting%20as%20political%20protest%20%E2%80%94%20an%20instrument%20often%20used%20by%20the%20most%20powerless%20(for%20example%2C%20prisoners%20in%20jail)%20to%20fight%20for%20their%20human%20rights.%C2%A0%20While%20de-criminalising%20attempted%20suicide%20as%20a%20general%20matter%2C%20BNS-IPC%20Clause%20224%20(%E2%80%9CAttempt%20to%20commit%20suicide%20to%20compel%20or%20restraint%20exercise%20of%20lawful%20power%E2%80%9D)%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhoever%20attempts%20to%20commit%20suicide%20with%20the%20intent%20to%20compel%20or%20restrain%20any%20public%20servant%20from%20discharging%20his%20official%20duty%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20simple%20imprisonment%20for%20a%20term%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20one%20year%20or%20with%20fine%20or%20with%20both%20or%20with%20community%20service.%E2%80%9D%20Its%20main%20purpose%20appears%20to%20only%20be%20to%20prohibit%20the%20use%20of%20fasting%20as%20a%20political%20weapon.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22The%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%20Allow%20the%20Govt%20to%20Decide%20Who%20Gets%20Booked%20and%20Who%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20for%20the%20Same%20Act%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-new-criminal-bills-allow-the-govt-to-decide-who-gets-booked-and-who-doesnt-for-the-same-act%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%20Allow%20the%20Govt%20to%20Decide%20Who%20Gets%20Booked%20and%20Who%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20for%20the%20Same%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EV.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EEncouraging%20force%20against%20assembly%20of%20persons%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fifth%20attack%20on%20our%20democratic%20rights%20is%20a%20strong%20statutory%20signalling%20by%20BNSS-CrPC%20to%20the%20police%20that%20force%20may%20be%20used%20against%20assemblies%20of%20people.%20Section%20130%20of%20the%20Cr.P.C.%20currently%20provides%20that%20if%20any%20unlawful%20assembly%2C%20or%20any%20assembly%20of%20five%20or%20more%20persons%20likely%20to%20cause%20a%20disturbance%20of%20the%20public%20peace%20cannot%20be%20otherwise%20dispersed%2C%20and%20if%20it%20is%20necessary%20for%20the%20public%20security%20that%20it%20should%20be%20dispersed%2C%20the%20Executive%20Magistrate%20of%20the%20highest%20rank%20who%20is%20present%20may%20cause%20it%20to%20be%20dispersed%20by%20the%20armed%20forces.%20Clause149%20of%20BNSS-CrPC%20tweaks%20this%20provision%20and%20says%20that%20in%20such%20circumstances%20the%20District%20Magistrate%20or%20any%20other%20Executive%20Magistrate%20authorised%20by%20him%2C%20who%20is%20present%20(i.e.%2C%20regardless%20of%20whether%20he%20is%20of%20the%20highest%20rank)%20may%20cause%20it%20to%20be%20dispersed%20by%20the%20armed%20forces.%E2%80%9D%20The%20tweaking%20serves%20as%20statutory%20signalling%20encouraging%20use%20of%20force%20to%20disperse%20assemblies%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVI.%20Shielding%20the%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3ESangh%20parivar%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20sixth%20attack%20is%20a%20partisan%20change%20of%20criminal%20statute%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Sangh%20%3Cem%3Eparivar%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20shielding%20it%20it%20from%20legal%20liability%20and%20allowing%20it%20greater%20space%20to%20operate%20against%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20noted%20earlier%2C%20the%20BNS-IPC%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20mirrors%20in%20part%20the%20European%20Council%20Framework%20Decision%20of%20June%2013%2C%202002%20under%20which%20terrorism%20is%20defined%20as%20offences%20under%20national%20law%20committed%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20%E2%80%9Cseriously%20destabilising%20or%20destroying%20the%20fundamental%20political%2C%20constitutional%2C%20economic%20or%20social%20structures%20of%20a%20country%20or%20an%20international%20organisation%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20attacks%20on%20the%20Constitutional%20structure%20are%20established%20offences%20under%20IPC%20and%20BNS-IPC%20including%2C%20for%20example%2C%20as%20attacks%20on%20the%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%2C%20it%20is%20very%20significant%20that%20the%20BNS-IPC%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20consciously%20omits%20attacks%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20structure%E2%80%9D.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20an%20act%20to%20destroy%20or%20destabilize%20the%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20structure%E2%80%9D%20of%20India%20would%20not%20be%20a%20terrorist%20act%20under%20BNS-IPC%2C%20terrorism%20whereas%20an%20act%20to%20destroy%20or%20destabilise%20the%20social%20structure%20of%20India%20(e.g%2C%20Varna%20system)%20would%20be%20a%20terrorist%20act%20even%20if%20it%20is%20not%20serious%20or%20fundamental!%20This%20customisation%20of%20the%20European%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20to%20omit%20attacks%20on%20the%20Constitutional%20structure%20of%20India%20from%20the%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20will%20allow%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%20to%20pursue%20its%20stated%20agenda%20of%20building%20a%20Hindu%20Rashtra%20polity%20in%20India%20which%20necessarily%20requires%20the%20destruction%20or%20destablisation%20of%20the%20current%20Constitutional%20structure%2C%20whether%20by%20stealth%20or%20by%20direct%20means%2C%20without%20it%20becoming%20terrorism.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20as%20noted%20earlier%2C%20BNS-IPC%20also%20makes%20it%20possible%20to%20stave%20off%20all%20acts%20seeking%20to%20destroy%20or%20destabilise%20the%20traditional%2C%20feudal%2C%20casteist%20social%20structure%20by%20including%20such%20acts%20within%20the%20definition%20of%20terrorist%20acts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%202005%20amendment%20had%20inserted%20section%20153AA%20into%20the%20IPC%20which%20criminalised%20carrying%20arms%20in%20any%20procession%20or%20organising%20or%20holding%20or%20taking%20part%20in%20any%20mass%20drill%20or%20mass%20training%20with%20arms%20in%20any%20public%20place%20in%20contravention%20of%20any%20public%20notice%20or%20order%20issued%20or%20made%20under%20section%20144A%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%201973%20(2%20of%201974)%2C%20with%20arms%20being%20defined%20as%20%E2%80%9Carticles%20of%20any%20description%20designed%20or%20adapted%20as%20weapons%20for%20offence%20or%20defence%20and%20includes%20firearms%2C%20sharp%20edged%20weapons%2C%20lathis%2C%20%3Cem%3Edandas%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20sticks.%E2%80%9D%20It%20is%20another%20matter%20that%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%20is%20so%20powerful%20regardless%20of%20which%20party%20rules%20India%20that%20Section%20144A%2C%20CrPC%20(%E2%80%9Cpower%20to%20prohibit%20carrying%20arms%20in%20procession%20or%20mass%20drill%20or%20mass%20training%20with%20arms%E2%80%9D)%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20brought%20into%20force%20through%20a%20simple%20notification%2C%2018%20years%20after%20its%20enactment.%20The%20two%20Sanhitas%20have%20quietly%20deleted%20both%20these%20provisions%20so%20that%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%20can%20happily%20continue%20armed%20training%20of%20its%20cadres%20without%20legal%20impediment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBNS-IPC%20Clause%20101%20introduces%20a%20new%20specific%20punishment%20for%20lynching%20which%20is%20defined%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmurder%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20race%2C%20caste%20or%20community%2C%20sex%2C%20place%20of%20birth%2C%20language%2C%20personal%20belief%20or%20any%20other%20ground%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CReligion%E2%80%9D%20is%20conveniently%20and%20noticeably%20left%20out%20as%20an%20enumerated%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVII.%20Exponentially%20enhancing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20police%20raj%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20seventh%20change%20proposed%20by%20the%20Bills%20puts%20a%20crucial%20power%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20police%2C%20which%20is%20a%20potential%20recipe%20for%20police%20excess.%20A%20draconian%20new%20BNSS-CrPC%20clause%20(Clause%20172)%20provides%20that%20%E2%80%9CAll%20persons%20shall%20be%20bound%20to%20conform%20to%20the%20lawful%20directions%20of%20a%20police%20officer%20given%20in%20fulfilment%20of%20any%20of%20his%20duty%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20The%20clause%20also%20provides%20that%20%E2%80%9CA%20police%20officer%20may%20detain%20or%20remove%20any%20person%20resisting%2C%20refusing%2C%20ignoring%20or%20disregarding%20to%20conform%20to%20any%20direction%20given%20by%20him%E2%80%A6%20and%20may%20either%20take%20such%20person%20before%20a%20Judicial%20Magistrate%20or%2C%20in%20petty%20cases%2C%20release%20him%20when%20the%20occasion%20is%20past.%E2%80%9D.%20Although%20the%20coercive%20action%20by%20a%20police%20officer%20detaining%20a%20person%20would%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20Constitutional%20law%20be%20an%20arrest%2C%20the%20suggestion%20seems%20to%20be%20that%20the%20detention%20may%20be%20done%20without%20complying%20with%20the%20Constitutional%20and%20statutory%20requirements%20for%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EVIII.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EBringing%20back%20h%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Eandcuff%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Es%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20eighth%20attack%20against%20Constitutional%20rights%20undermines%20decades%20old%20judicially%20created%20restrictions%20against%20use%20of%20handcuffs.%20In%20the%201978%20judgment%20in%20%3Cem%3ESunil%20Batra%20v.%20Delhi%20Administration%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CFetters%2C%20especially%20bar%20fetters%2C%20shall%20be%20shunned%20as%20violative%20of%20human%20dignity%2C%20within%20and%20without%20prisons.%20The%20indiscriminate%20resort%20to%20handcuffs%20when%20accused%20persons%20are%20taken%20to%20and%20from%20court%20and%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.manupatrafast.in%2Fpers%2Fviewdoctoc.aspx%3FsPath%3DSupremeCourt%2FSupremeCourt%2F1950-1979%2Fsc1978%2Fs780431.htm%5C%22%3Eexpedient%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20forcing%20irons%20on%20prison%20inmates%20are%20illegal%20and%20shall%20be%20stopped%20forthwith%20save%20in%20a%20small%20category%20of%20cases%20dealt%20with%20next%20below.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.manupatrafast.in%2Fpers%2Fviewdoctoc.aspx%3FsPath%3DSupremeCourt%2FSupremeCourt%2F1950-1979%2Fsc1978%2Fs780431.htm%5C%22%3EReckless%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0handcuffing%20and%20chaining%20in%20public%20degrades%2C%20puts%20to%20shame%20finer%20sensibilities%20and%20is%20a%20slur%20on%20our%20culture.%E2%80%9D%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20reiterated%20in%20%3Cem%3EPrem%20Shankar%20Shukla%20v.%20Delhi%20Administration%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CTo%20prevent%20the%20escape%20of%20an%20under-trial%20is%20in%20public%20interest%2C%20reasonable%2C%20just%20and%20cannot%2C%20by%20itself%20be%20castigated.%20But%20to%20bind%20a%20man%20hand%20and%20foot%2C%20fetter%20his%20limbs%20with%20hoops%20of%20steel%2C%20shuffle%20him%20along%20in%20the%20streets%20and%20stand%20him%20for%20hours%20in%20the%20courts%20is%20to%20torture%20him%2C%20defile%20his%20dignity%2C%20vulgarise%20society%20and%20foul%20the%20soul%20of%20our%20Constitutional%20culture.%E2%80%9D%20Undermining%20the%20Constitutional%20ethos%20that%20lies%20behind%20these%20judgment%2C%20Clause%2043(3)%20of%20BNSS-CrPC%20provides%20that%20%E2%80%9CThe%20police%20officer%20may%2C%20keeping%20in%20view%20the%20nature%20and%20gravity%20of%20the%20offence%2C%20use%20handcuff%20(sic)%20while%20effecting%20the%20arrest%20of%20a%20person%20who%20is%20a%20habitual%2C%20repeat%20offender%20who%20escaped%20from%20custody%2C%20who%20has%20committed%20offence%20of%20organised%20crime%2C%20offence%20of%20terrorist%20act%2C%20drug%20related%20crime%2C%20or%20offence%20of%20illegal%20possession%20of%20arms%20and%20ammunition%2C%20murder%2C%20rape%2C%20acid%20attack%2C%20counterfeiting%20of%20coins%20and%20currency%20notes%2C%20human%20trafficking%2C%20sexual%20offences%20against%20children%2C%20offences%20against%20the%20State%2C%20including%20acts%20endangering%20sovereignty%2C%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%20or%20economic%20offences.%E2%80%9D%20This%20mechanical%20enumeration%20of%20specific%20crimes%20in%20which%20the%20police%20may%20use%20handcuffs%20will%20be%20applied%20as%20statutory%20licence%20to%20routinely%20use%20handcuffs%20in%20most%2C%20if%20not%20all%2C%20cases%20involving%20the%20listed%20offences.%20It%20will%20then%20soon%20infect%20the%20general%20police%20practice%20and%20resurrect%20the%20medieval%20culture%20of%20routinely%20shackling%20human%20beings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Shoddy%20Drafting%20Has%20Left%20the%20Government's%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%20With%20Glaring%20Errors%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcriminal-bills-drafting-shoddy-sakshya-nyay-sanhita-ipc-evidence%5C%22%3EShoddy%20Drafting%20Has%20Left%20the%20Government%E2%80%99s%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%20With%20Glaring%20Errors%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIX.%20Maximising%20police%20custody%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20ninth%20attack%20on%20our%20freedom%20is%20the%20maximisation%20by%20BNSS-CrPC%20(Clause%20187%20(2))%20of%20dreaded%20police%20custody%20during%20investigation.%20Under%20current%20law%2C%20as%20held%20by%20the%20Supreme%20court%20of%20India%20in%20%3Cem%3EState%20(Delhi%20Administration)%20vs.%20Dharam%20Pal%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1982)%20and%20%3Cem%3ECBI%20vs.%20Anupam%20J.%20Kulkarn%3C%2Fem%3Ei%20(1992)%2C%20the%20accused%20can%20be%20sent%20to%20police%20custody%20only%20for%20up%20to%20fifteen%20days%20within%20the%20first%20fifteen%20days%20of%20the%20accused%20being%20presented%20before%20the%20Magistrate%20after%20his%20or%20her%20arrest%2C%20even%20if%20the%20actual%20number%20of%20days%20for%20which%20the%20police%20may%20get%20custody%20in%20that%20period%20is%20less%20than%20fifteen%20days.%20Clause%20187%20(2)%20of%20BNSS-CrPC%20over-rules%20this%20judicial%20dictum%20and%20provides%20that%20the%20Judicial%20Magistrate%20may%20give%20police%20custody%20for%20a%20term%20not%20exceeding%20fifteen%20days%20in%20the%20whole%2C%20or%20in%20parts%2C%20at%20any%20time%20during%20the%20initial%20forty%20days%20or%20sixty%20days%20out%20of%20the%20maximum%20detention%20period%20of%20sixty%20days%20(for%20offences%20punishable%20with%20imprisonment%20for%20less%20than%20ten%20years)%20or%20ninety%20days%20(for%20offences%20punishable%20with%20death%20or%20imprisonment%20for%20life%20or%20imprisonment%20for%20a%20term%20of%20not%20less%20than%20ten%20years).%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20threat%20of%20police%20custody%20will%20hang%20over%20the%20heads%20of%20the%20accused%20during%20the%20entire%20investigation%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F11082632%2FImage6.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F11082632%2FImage6.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F11082632%2FImage6-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F11082632%2FImage6-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-508921%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EX.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EForcing%20provision%20of%20b%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Eiometrics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20tenth%20attack%20on%20peoples%E2%80%99%20Constitutional%20right%20to%20privacy%20is%20the%20unreasonable%20and%20excessive%20compulsion%20created%20against%20all%20persons%20to%20provide%20specimen%20signatures%2C%20finger%20impressions%2C%20handwriting%20or%20voice%20samples%20in%20connection%20with%20an%20investigation%20even%20if%20he%20or%20she%20is%20not%20an%20accused%20person.%20Clause%20349%20of%20BNSS-CrPC%20provides%20that%20a%20magistrate%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20direct%20any%20person%2C%20including%C2%A0%20an%20accused%20person%2C%20to%20give%20specimen%20signatures%20or%20finger%20impressions%20or%20handwriting%20or%20voice%20sample%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20Clause%20349%20of%20BNSS-CrPC%20mainstreams%20and%20integrates%20into%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmother%E2%80%9D%20penal%20law%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20recent%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(Identification)%20Act%2C%202022%20which%20gives%20power%20to%20a%20police%20officer%20or%20a%20prison%20officer%20to%20compulsorily%20take%20from%20convicts%20and%20persons%20arrested%20in%20connection%20with%20an%20offence%20punishable%20under%20any%20law%20for%20the%20time%20being%20in%20force%20or%20detained%20under%20any%20preventive%20detention%20law%20%E2%80%9Cmeasurements%E2%80%9D%20(including%20finger-impressions%2C%20palm-print%20impressions%2C%20foot-print%20impressions%2C%20photographs%2C%20iris%20and%20retina%20scan%2C%20physical%2C%20biological%20samples%20and%20their%20analysis%2C%20behavioural%20attributes%20including%20signatures%2C%20handwriting%20or%20any%20other%20examination%20referred%20to%20in%20section%2053%20or%20section%2053A%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C1973%20(except%20that%20a%20person%20arrested%20other%20than%20for%20an%20offence%20committed%20against%20a%20woman%20or%20a%20child%20or%20for%20an%20offence%20punishable%20with%20imprisonment%20of%20seven%20years%20or%20more)%20is%20not%20obliged%20to%20allow%20taking%20of%20biological%20samples).%20The%20impact%20of%20clause%20349%20of%20BNSS-CrPC%20is%20that%20even%20persons%20not%20falling%20under%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(Identification)%20Act%2C%202022%20(i.e.%2C%20convicts%20and%20arrested%20persons)%20will%20also%20now%20be%20liable%20to%20be%20forced%20by%20a%20magistrate%20to%20provide%20her%20or%20his%20%E2%80%9Cmeasurements%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EXI.%20Enhanc%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Eing%20discretionary%20power%20of%20police%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%2011th%20change%20that%20enhances%20the%20discretionary%20power%20of%20the%20police%20in%20relation%20to%20crimes%20committed%20against%20powerless%20victims%20is%20the%20reversal%20of%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20in%20%3Cem%3ELalita%20Kumari%20vs.%20Government%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2014)%20that%20every%20information%20received%20by%20a%20police%20station%20must%20be%20recorded%20as%20a%20first%20information%20report%20and%20investigated%20even%20if%20the%20police%20is%20not%20satisfied%20with%20the%20reasonableness%20or%20credibility%20of%20the%20information.%20This%20judicial%20decision%20responded%20to%20the%20reality%20that%20powerful%20people%20can%20ensure%20that%20no%20FIR%20is%20registered%20and%20no%20investigation%20is%20conducted%20based%20on%20information%20provided%20by%20powerless%20people%20with%20respect%20to%20crimes%20committed%20by%20the%20powerful%20against%20them.%20Clause%20173(3)%20of%20BNSS-CrPC%20would%20now%20make%20the%20recording%20of%20a%20FIR%20discretionary%20for%20the%20police.%20The%20police%20will%20have%20the%20power%20to%20conduct%20a%20preliminary%20enquiry%20to%20ascertain%20whether%20there%20exists%20a%20prima%20facie%20case%20before%20proceeding%20to%20investigate%20information%20alleging%20commission%20of%20a%20cognizable%20offence%20punishable%20with%20imprisonment%20between%20three%20years%20and%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EXII.%20Intensifying%20the%20pain%20of%20imprisonment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%2012th%20attack%20on%20democracy%20is%20the%20enhancement%20of%20incarceration.%20While%20there%20is%20a%20poorly%20developed%20and%20limited%20introduction%20of%20community%20service%20as%20a%20limited%20alternative%20punishment%2C%20the%20Bills%20increase%20the%20length%20of%20imprisonment%20virtually%20across%20the%20board%2C%20almost%20routinely.%20The%20Indian%20list%20of%20capital%20offences%20and%20offences%20punishable%20with%20life%20imprisonment%20was%20already%20much%20too%20long%20for%20a%20democracy%20under%20existing%20law%2C%20reflecting%20the%20draconian%20approach%20adopted%20by%20even%20social%20democratic%20governments%20that%20largely%20ruled%20India%20until%20a%20decade%20ago.%C2%A0%20The%20new%20Bills%20add%20at%20least%20three%20new%20capital%20offences%20and%20six%20life%20sentences%20to%20this%20list.%20While%20life%20imprisonment%20that%20must%20mandatorily%20last%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20convict%E2%80%99s%20natural%20life%20(as%20against%2014%20years)%20is%20now%20confined%20to%20a%20few%20offences%2C%20Clause%204(b)%20of%20BNS-IPC%20makes%20imprisonment%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20convict%E2%80%99s%20natural%20life%20the%20only%20form%20of%20life%20imprisonment%20in%20India.%20The%20possibility%20of%20house%20arrest%20of%20under-trials%20is%20ruled%20out%20by%20the%20new%20BNSS-CrPC%20Clause%20187(5)%20which%20provides%20that%20%E2%80%9Cno%20person%20shall%20be%20detained%20otherwise%20than%20in%20police%20station%20under%20police%20custody%20or%20in%20prison%20under%20judicial%20custody%20or%20place%20declared%20as%20prison%20by%20the%20Central%20Government%20or%20the%20State%20Government.%E2%80%9D%20Under-trials%20from%20marginalised%20social%20groups%20constitute%20the%20bulk%20of%20inmates%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20over-crowded%20and%20inhumane%20prisons%20where%20their%20incarceration%20becomes%20punishment%20even%20before%20they%20are%20convicted.%20Closing%20this%20door%20and%20forcing%20them%20all%20to%20be%20in%20jail%2C%20shows%20that%20one%20of%20the%20objectives%20of%20these%20reforms%20is%20to%20make%20the%20process%20the%20punishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20laws%20seek%20to%20make%20a%20Stan%20Swamy%20of%20us%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Know%20The%20Three%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%3A%20What's%20New%20and%20What's%20Old%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fknow-the-three-new-criminal-bills-whats-new-and-whats-old%5C%22%3EKnow%20The%20Three%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%3A%20What%E2%80%99s%20New%20and%20What%E2%80%99s%20Old%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOverview%20and%20conclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20had%20several%20law%20commission%20reports%20and%20reform%20committee%20reports%20that%20have%20recommended%20changes%20to%20criminal%20law%20over%20the%20years%20%E2%80%94%20indeed%20it%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20principal%20topics%20of%20the%20work%20of%20the%20law%20commission.%20We%20have%20always%20been%20able%20to%20understand%20and%20analyse%20the%20goals%20and%20rationale%20guiding%20proposed%20amendments%20to%20the%20law%20from%20these%20reports.%20This%20is%20the%20first%20time%2C%20however%2C%20that%20we%20do%20not%20have%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20report%20of%20the%20committee%20that%20drafted%20three%20new%20statutes%20because%2C%20if%20there%20is%20such%20a%20report%20beyond%20the%20draft%2C%20it%20is%20not%20publicly%20available.%20A%20very%20important%20unanswered%20question%20is%20why%20was%20it%20necessary%20to%20repeal%20the%20existing%20laws%20and%20enact%20three%20new%20laws%3F%20Separately%2C%20it%20must%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20draft%20Bills%20are%20riddled%20with%20drafting%20errors%20and%20typos.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20then%20still%20draft%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20Thomas%20Macaulay%2C%20the%20principal%20draftsman%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20said%20in%20a%20speech%20delivered%20to%20the%20U.K.%20House%20of%20Commons%20on%20the%2010th%20of%20July%201833%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20propose%20no%20rash%20innovation%3B%20we%20wish%20to%20give%20no%20shock%20to%20the%20prejudices%20of%20any%20part%20of%20our%20subjects.%20Our%20principle%20is%20simply%20this%3B%20uniformity%20where%20you%20can%20have%20it%3A%20diversity%20where%20you%20must%20have%20it%3B%20but%20in%20all%20cases%20certainty.%E2%80%9D%20If%20there%20is%20anything%20colonial%20that%20has%20been%20rejected%20in%20the%20new%20language%20proposed%20in%20the%20two%20Sanhitas%20and%20the%20Adhiniyam%2C%20it%20is%20this%20precept.%20At%20least%20for%20now%2C%20however%2C%20this%20precept%20remains%20a%20part%20of%20the%20inviolable%20Constitutional%20basic%20feature%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20rule%20of%20law%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20overall%20flavour%20of%20the%20changes%20sought%20to%20be%20made%20by%20the%20new%20statutes%20is%20captured%20by%20a%20relatively%20minor%20change%20of%20vocabulary.%20The%20current%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20refers%20to%20the%20local%20and%20district%20criminal%20courts%20as%20%E2%80%9Ccourts%20of%20justice%E2%80%9D.%20There%20are%20at%20least%20some%2039%20such%20references%20in%20the%20IPC.%20This%20vocabulary%20is%20a%20gentle%20reminder%20to%20the%20judges%20who%20sit%20in%20these%20courts%20that%20they%20are%20guardians%20of%20justice%2C%20sitting%20as%20sentinels%20against%20injustice%20by%20the%20executive%2C%20that%20they%20are%20not%20mere%20extensions%20of%20the%20law%20and%20order%20machinery%2C%20not%20police%20in%20black%20more%20concerned%20with%20increasing%20conviction%20rates%20(a%20main%20goal%20identified%20by%20the%20Union%20in%20this%20reform%20exercise)%20and%20throwing%20people%20in%20jail%20than%20with%20justice.%20Sadly%2C%20the%20new%20BNS-IPC%20entirely%20drops%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Ccourt%20of%20justice%E2%80%9D%20and%20refers%20to%20these%20courts%20merely%20as%20%E2%80%9Ccourts%E2%80%9D.%20Perhaps%20the%20drafting%20committee%20found%20that%20%E2%80%9Cjustice%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20colonial%20idea%20that%20had%20to%20expurgated%20from%20criminal%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20ethos%20of%20these%20provisions%20is%20not%20drawn%20from%20our%20secular%2C%20democratic%2C%20republican%20constitution%20and%20its%20idea%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20power%20emanating%20from%20the%20people.%20It%20is%20drawn%20from%20the%20ethos%20of%20religion%20%E2%80%94%20where%20dharma%2C%20laid%20down%20by%20God%20and%20administered%20by%20rulers%20and%20priests%2C%20is%20the%20source%20of%20law%20and%20is%20to%20be%20obeyed%20unquestioningly%20by%20people.%20The%20names%20of%20the%20Bills%20are%20significant%20in%20this%20regard%3A%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20(the%20collection%20of%20Bharatiya%20justice%20which%20is%20based%20on%20Sanatana%20Dharma)%3B%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20(the%20collection%20of%20Bharatiya%20security%20for%20citizens%2C%20drawn%20from%20Sanatana%20Dharma)%3B%20and%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Adhiniyam%20(the%20law%20of%20Bharatiya%20Evidence).%20The%20name%20%E2%80%9CBharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20keystone%20law%20is%20of%20special%20significance.%20Although%20the%20literal%20meaning%20of%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9CSanhita%E2%80%9D%20is%20%E2%80%9Ccollection%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20is%20widely%20understood%20as%20referring%20to%20a%20collection%20of%20hymns%20and%20mantras%20in%20each%20of%20the%20Vedas.%20The%20Manusmriti%2C%20known%20for%20its%20discriminatory%20content%2C%20is%20also%20known%20as%20a%20Sanhita.%20This%20is%20the%20first%20time%20that%20a%20statute%20in%20India%20is%20being%20given%20a%20theocratic%20name%20%E2%80%94%20not%20any%20%E2%80%9Cordinary%E2%80%9D%20statute%2C%20but%20the%20most%20consequential%20legal%20instrument%20in%20our%20country%20after%20the%20Constitution.%20This%20change%20of%20nomenclature%20reveals%20the%20intent%20and%20essence%20of%20the%20criminal%20law%20reform.%20It%20is%20a%20modest%20start%20of%20the%20process%20of%20shifting%20the%20foundation%20of%20our%20legal%20system%20from%20constitutional%20to%20theocratic%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Eshilanyas%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20Hindu%20legal%20system%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20not%20a%20single%20liberal%20strand%20in%20any%20of%20the%20changes%20made%20in%20the%20law.%20The%20entire%20IPC%20toolkit%20now%20selectively%20targeted%20against%20liberal%20voices%20is%20retained%20in%20the%20new%20Sanhitas%20including%20%E2%80%98promoting%20enmity%20between%20different%20groups%20on%20grounds%20of%20religion%2C%20race%2C%20place%20of%20birth%2C%20residence%2C%20language%20and%20doing%20acts%20prejudicial%20to%20the%20maintenance%20of%20harmony%E2%80%99%3B%20%E2%80%98statements%20creating%20or%20promoting%20enmity%2C%20hatred%20or%20ill-will%20between%20classes%E2%80%99%3B%E2%80%98imputations%20prejudicial%20to%20national%20integration%E2%80%99%3B%E2%80%98deliberate%20and%20malicious%20acts%20intended%20to%20outrage%20religious%20feelings%20of%20any%20class%20by%20insulting%20its%20religion%20or%20religious%20beliefs%3B%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98uttering%20words%2C%20etc.%2C%20with%20deliberate%20intent%20to%20wound%20the%20religious%20feelings%20of%20any%20person%E2%80%99.%20An%20epochal%20change%20such%20as%20the%20introduction%20of%20an%20entirely%20new%20set%20of%20criminal%20laws%20is%20also%20a%20huge%20missed%20opportunity%20to%20correct%20the%20skewed%20balance%20in%20our%20criminal%20law%20in%20favour%20of%20protecting%20state%20power%20and%20wealth%20as%20against%20protecting%20individual%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20home%20minister%20has%20repeatedly%20said%20that%20the%20purpose%20of%20the%20reforms%20is%20to%20decolonize%20criminal%20law%20and%20put%20in%20place%20laws%20%E2%80%9Cimbibed%20with%20the%20Indian%20soul%E2%80%9D.%20This%20is%20far%20from%20the%20truth.%20That%20the%20aim%20of%20the%20new%20laws%20is%20to%20decolonize%20criminal%20law%20is%20at%20best%20a%20populist%20political%20claim.%20The%20fact%2C%20in%20the%20words%20of%20a%20scholar%20of%20the%20subject%2C%20is%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccriminal%20law%20in%20the%20British%20Empire%20was%20neither%20fully%20benevolent%20nor%20fully%20despotic%2C%20constrained%20by%20race%20and%20inequality%20in%20one%20direction%2C%20and%20constitutionalism%20and%20an%20ideological%20adherence%20to%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20in%20the%20other.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20proposed%20amendments%20embrace%2C%20retain%20and%20enlarge%20most%20of%20the%20despotic%20colonial%20content%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20in%20letter%20and%20in%20spirit.%20The%20colonial%20soul%20is%20safely%20ensconced%20in%20the%20two%20Sanhitas.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20what%20is%20decolonised%20is%20the%20progressive%20content%20of%20the%20colonial%20code%20such%20as%20the%20ideologies%20of%20constitutionalism%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20face%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20tests%20in%20its%20history%20when%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20three%20Bills%20are%20challenged%20once%20they%20are%20enacted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECriminal%20law%20deeply%20affects%20the%20common%20masses.%20Apart%20from%20crimes%20committed%20by%20the%20state%20and%20powerful%20segments%20of%20society%2C%20crime%20is%20for%20the%20most%20part%20violence%20by%20poor%20males%20against%20poor%20males%20and%20females.%20The%20common%20people%20of%20India%20will%20therefore%20look%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20an%20accurate%20determination%20of%20the%20existence%2C%20non-%20existence%2C%20nature%20or%20extent%20of%20their%20fundamental%20rights%20and%20the%20protection%20of%20these%20rights%20against%20the%20all-powerful%20state%2C%20not%20a%20balancing%20of%20their%20rights%20against%20the%20interests%20of%20an%20anti-Constitutional%20ideological%20movement%20acting%20as%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EG.%20Mohan%20Gopal%20is%20an%20advocate%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20and%20a%20renowned%20legal%20academician.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698559241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F29015445%2FIMG_2557.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-three-criminal-law-bills-using-criminal-law-to-establish-permanent-extra-constitutional-emergency-powers%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CDon%E2%80%99t%20give%20them%20space%20to%20breathe!%E2%80%9D%20Twelve%20changes%20to%20criminal%20law%20in%20the%20three%20Bills%20introduced%20in%20parliament%20in%20August%2C%202023%20will%20create%20a%20quantum%20leap%20in%20the%20power%20of%20the%20government%2C%20if%20and%20when%20it%20so%20wishes%2C%20to%20silence%20dissent%20and%20opposition%20and%20shut%20down%20public%20discourse%2C%20choking%20all%20channels%20that%20communicate%20conflicting%20news%20or%20views%20to%20the%20people.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-three-criminal-law-bills-using-criminal-law-to-establish-permanent-extra-constitutional-emergency-powers%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22FP